                           (cp. <foreign xml:lang="gez">sǝtebǝr</foreign>) of an unspecified year.</note>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="a10">
                           <locus target="#78r"/>
                           <desc type="ProtectivePrayer"/>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ጰውሎ፡ ወሬዩዊና፡ ፈላዊና፡ ፈላፎት፡ ፈላፎት፡ ፈላፎት፡ ጻጻጻ፡ <choice>
                                 <sic>አኃዚሆ፡</sic>
                              </choice> ፫ቃላተ፡ አልፍ፡ <supplied reason="omitted">ኤፍ፡</supplied> 
                              ካፍ፡ በዝንቱ፡ <choice>
                                 <sic>እስማት፡</sic>
                              </choice> 
                              <choice>
                                 <sic>እሰር፡</sic>
                              </choice> እደዊሆሙ፡ ወእገሪሆሙ፡ ወአድክም፡ አብራኪሆሙ፡ 
                              ወአ<supplied reason="omitted">ጽ</supplied>ልም፡ አእይ<supplied reason="omitted">ን</supplied>ቲሆሙ፡ <choice>
                                 <sic>ለጸናሕያን፡</sic>
                              </choice> 
                              ፍኖት፡ <choice>
                                 <sic>ወለተትአጋልያነ፡</sic>
                              </choice> ንዋይ፡ <choice>
                                 <sic>ወለካአውያነ፡</sic>
                              </choice> ደም፡ እስከ፡ አሐልፍ፡ አነ፡ ዮሀንስ፡ ምስለ፡ 
                              <choice>
                                 <sic>ኩሉ፡</sic>
                              </choice> ንዋይየ፡ ወጥሪትየ፡  
                           </q>
                           <note>The note was written by a certain Yoḥannǝs (perhaps <persName ref="PRS11327Yohannes"/>). It contains magical names to protect 
                              him along the way. The same prayer is also contained in <ref type="item" corresp="BAVet45#a1"/>.
                           The word <q xml:lang="gez">ፌርቤዮ፡</q>, i.e. "february", is written in the lower margin of the same leaf.</note>
                        </item>
                    
